        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 13 at 3:16PM CDT by NWS Jackson MS</headline>
        <description>At 315 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Vernon, or 12 miles southeast of Bay Springs, moving southeast at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Sandersville and Heidelberg around 320 PM CDT.
Mill Creek around 340 PM CDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
